								<div class="title" id="post-title-4072834">
																		Everything Must End
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164149" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;" >djkaktus</a></span> <span class="odate time_1543645248 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Dec 2018 06:20</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4072834">
									

<div style="text-align: center;">
<blockquote>
<p>People play this great charade<br />
And always miss the point<br />
Never fall for prophecies</p>
<p><em>The Way It Ends</em> by Prototype</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
<p>This is the culmination of several years worth of effort, far more than I've ever invested into anything else on the wiki. It would not have been possible without considerable contributions and creative inspiration from Hippo and ARD, as well as a myriad of other persons who have looked at this over the last few months in preparation for today.</p>
<p>Including:</p>
<p>Conceptual Workshopping by Hippo<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-759404-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-759404-1')">1</a></sup> &amp; ARD,</p>
<p>Critique by Hippo, ARD, Conwell, Modulum, Yossi, Westrin, Vessel, Ratking, taylor, Adriatica, and a variety of others,</p>
<p>Formatting assistance by Croquembouche and ChaoSera</p>
<p>Images by SunnyClockwork (and me!)</p>
<p>The Way It Ends theme (nu-SCP variant) and all accompanying images were created by Woedenaz. Bless him.</p>
<p>This is the final part in a series that began with The Children and continued with The Broken God. I hope you enjoy it.</p>
